      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 (FD) features the legendary 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine, delivering a linear power band and exceptional power-to-weight ratio. The longitudinal front-midship layout ensures 50:50 weight distribution, complemented by a four-wheel double-wishbone suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential for superior lateral grip. Recent service includes a full vacuum line simplification and cooling system refresh to maintain optimal thermal efficiency. The five-speed manual gearbox offers short, precise throws with no synchro grind. While the exterior shows minor road wear consistent with a well-loved driver\u2019s car, the internal mechanicals\u2014including apex seal compression and boost pressure\u2014remain within factory specifications. This R2-trim example includes dual oil coolers and a strut tower brace, making it a mechanically robust platform for the purist enthusiast.",
